        content: "Lincoln-Douglas (LD) debate is one of the most elegant and challenging debate formats. Named after the famous 1858 debates between Abraham Lincoln and Stephen Douglas, this format puts you center stage—alone—to argue profound questions of values and philosophy.\n\nIn this lesson, we'll explore LD debate in depth:\n• The one-on-one nature and what it means for preparation\n• The value-based approach to argumentation\n• The complete time structure (6-3-7-3-4-6-3)\n• The roles of Affirmative and Negative\n• How a typical LD round unfolds\n\nBy the end, you'll understand exactly how LD works and be ready to start building your first case.",
