        content: "LD follows a precise time structure that every debater must know. The sequence is: 6-3-7-3-4-6-3.\n\n**1. Affirmative Constructive (AC): 6 minutes**\nThe Affirmative presents their complete case, including:\n• Value and value criterion\n• Contentions supporting the resolution\n• Framework for why their value matters most\n\n**2. Cross-Examination by Negative: 3 minutes**\nThe Negative asks the Affirmative questions to:\n• Clarify arguments\n• Expose weaknesses\n• Set up their own arguments\n\n**3. Negative Constructive (NC): 7 minutes**\nThe Negative's main speech, which must:\n• Present their own case (value, criterion, contentions)\n• Attack the Affirmative's case\n• Manage time between offense and defense\n\n**4. Cross-Examination by Affirmative: 3 minutes**\nThe Affirmative questions the Negative\n\n**5. First Affirmative Rebuttal (1AR): 4 minutes**\nThe hardest speech in LD. The Affirmative must:\n• Respond to everything the Negative said\n• Rebuild their own case\n• In half the time the Negative had!\n\n**6. Negative Rebuttal (NR): 6 minutes**\nThe Negative's final speech:\n• Extends winning arguments\n• Crystallizes voting issues\n• Explains why they should win\n\n**7. Second Affirmative Rebuttal (2AR): 3 minutes**\nThe final speech of the debate:\n• Answers the Negative Rebuttal\n• Crystallizes the Affirmative's path to victory\n• Makes the final impression on the judge",
