        content: "Policy Debate has the most speeches of any format—eight total, plus four cross-examinations.\n\n**The Complete Structure:**\n\n**1. First Affirmative Constructive (1AC) - 8 minutes**\nPresents the entire Affirmative case including plan, inherency, significance, and advantages.\n\n**2. Cross-Examination of 1AC - 3 minutes**\n2N questions 1A\n\n**3. First Negative Constructive (1NC) - 8 minutes**\nPresents Negative positions: off-case (DAs, counterplans, topicality, kritiks) and case attacks.\n\n**4. Cross-Examination of 1NC - 3 minutes**\n1A questions 1N\n\n**5. Second Affirmative Constructive (2AC) - 8 minutes**\nResponds to everything in the 1NC—answers all Negative arguments.\n\n**6. Cross-Examination of 2AC - 3 minutes**\n1N questions 2A\n\n**7. Second Negative Constructive (2NC) - 8 minutes**\nExtends and develops Negative positions, especially those 2AC under-covered.\n\n**8. Cross-Examination of 2NC - 3 minutes**\n2A questions 2N\n\n**9. First Negative Rebuttal (1NR) - 5 minutes**\nCovers different arguments than 2NC (they divide the block).\n\n**10. First Affirmative Rebuttal (1AR) - 5 minutes**\nMust respond to 13 minutes of Negative (2NC + 1NR) in just 5.\n\n**11. Second Negative Rebuttal (2NR) - 5 minutes**\nNarrows to winning arguments, crystallizes.\n\n**12. Second Affirmative Rebuttal (2AR) - 5 minutes**\nFinal speech—must win the debate.",
