        content: "Public Forum (PF) Debate was created in 2002 with a specific goal: make competitive debate accessible to both participants and audiences. If Policy is the specialist's format and LD is the philosopher's format, Public Forum is the citizen's format—debates about real issues that real people care about.\n\nIn this lesson, you'll learn:\n• How the two-person team format works\n• Why current events topics change monthly\n• How PF is designed for lay (non-expert) audiences\n• The complete speech and crossfire structure\n• Strategies for success in Public Forum\n\nBy the end, you'll understand why PF has become one of the fastest-growing debate formats and how it might be the perfect entry point for your debate journey.",
